⚖️ **Data Representation**
• 📝 **Use Standard Notation**: Styles include: distance "32 m" and "32 m"; temperature "18 °C" or "18 °C"; weight "55 kg" or "65 t";

🔍 **Identify Patterns**
• 💡 **Look for Consistency**: Temperature is represented by two decimal places, while weight is represented in both metric (kg) and imperial (t) units;

📊 **Use Abbreviations Wisely**
• 🗂️ **Limit Use of Abbreviations**: Only use abbreviations when necessary to avoid confusion; otherwise, spell out the full term.
